Body: How does pow differ from lpow?

Author: Korporal
Title: [ANN] GAMEMACHINE.IO - simple and transparent investments in game industry!
Body: Difference from classical Proof-of-Work in which equipment power directly influences awards and creates “a power race” creating many negative factors, such as: the difficult entrance of new participants, forces to make investments in the equipment, but not in development of network, strong increase in consumption of electricity, etc. LPoW allows to remove these problems, having made access to a possibility of use of PoW limited.

Author: Kruger1863
Title: [ANN] GAMEMACHINE.IO - simple and transparent investments in game industry!
Body: Stay away from buying this tokens. You buy GMIT tokens but they have something called GMC which is supposed to be a reward for gamers for mining. They said these GMC coins will be transformed into Gamefuel tradable cryptocurrency AS WELL as GMIT tokens. The problem is that these GMC tokens currently are not tokens but just server-side points giving to gamers for mining ETH and ZEC for them in their app. They give and grab GMC points whenever they want. So the exact future amount of Gamefuel and exchange rate are unpredictable. Here is how they have changed their concept on the fly even here on bitcointalk:  https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2352604.20  This is Russian-language topic but you can use built-in Google Translate in Chrome to catch the point. Look at the end of page 2. Exchange rate for GMC-GMIT was 0.2 then became 0.0002 during discussion. When I came to their mining app rate was 0.00057. Currently it is 0.00014. If you google you'll find even different rates for GMIT-Gamefuel. What's next?  Beta app for gamers currently is almost unusable. Almost all the time people can't withdraw items they have bought for GMC points. One day there was a bug with unlimited GMC coins gained by users (trillions of coins). Good for them they had fixed it in an hour. Then they zeroed balances and CEO promised that it would be possible to withdraw all items bought. Then they zeroed those items. After that they drastically reduced mining reward in GMC and declared that there was so-called "too fast x10 mining bug" before "billions bug". Yeah, they didn't see x10 reward for several days ;D Looks like they simply adjust GMC reward just for marketing purposes or to control the size of withdraw queue. And all that centralized and "dynamic" GMC will become tradable Gamefuel? Okaay.  Finally I can't say this is a 100% scam. But obviously guys are not so experienced and solid team they want to seem. My personal opinion they can't handle such a vast idea described in their roadmap. Although graphic designer is great.  P.S. Forgot to say that people are constantly complaining about unexpected huge shortage of received GMITs after paying (see their Telegram channel). Every time guys answered that there were some third-party fees and they would handle it personally.
